    <text id="A9816T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p> J. S. Calvert describes financial matters for Alexander H. H. Stuart.</p>
            </div1>

        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>Treasury Office of Virginia, Richmond 
                    <name type="recipient">Hon. A. H. H. Stuart</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-01-21">January 21st, 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Richmond</name>
                        
                    </dateline>
                    <salute><abbr expan="Dear">Dr</abbr> sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Yours of the 18<hi rend="super">th</hi> inst is before me, and I submit the
                    following as the result of the examination you desired-- <lb/>1866. January 1.
                    Your credit in stocks 29.700 <lb/>'' Feby 29 Transfered to W.L.C. Trustee <hi
                        rend="underline">26.000</hi>
                    <lb/>leaving in your name <hi rend="underline">$3.700</hi>
                    <lb/>The <abbr expan="Interest">Int.</abbr> due 1 January '66 on 29.700 --
                    $1782. <lb/>Funded A. H. H. Stuart on 3.700 222<lb/>'' W L Clark 7<hi
                        rend="super">20</hi>
                    <lb/>Subject to order of W. B. Clark <hi rend="underline">480</hi> 1422
                    <lb/>leaving to credit of <hi rend="underline">somebody</hi> $360 <lb/>This, I
                    presume will be claimed by W. L. Clark on the $3000 <abbr expan="transferred"
                            >transf<hi rend="super">d</hi></abbr> to him <abbr expan="January"
                    >Jany</abbr> 18. 1867.</p>
                <p>The <abbr expan="Interest">Int.</abbr>
                    <hi rend="underline">for the year 1866</hi>
                    <add hand="h1" place="inline">on 26,000</add> is not funded -- and standing to
                    credit of W. L. G. Trustee -- $1560. The certificates for the 2% <hi
                        rend="underline">deferred interest</hi> have issued to W. L. C.</p>


                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Truly <abbr expan="Yours">Yrs</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>J. S. Calvert</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
